gives him immunity or something.

527
00:48:04,132 --> 00:48:07,844
Valchek gave him immunity
and he just put valchek on his ass.

528
00:48:10,472 --> 00:48:14,976
- Nothing since the fort Howard meet.
- They're dumping phones.

529
00:48:17,437 --> 00:48:19,439
- Lester.
- Mm?

530
00:48:20,774 --> 00:48:25,153
When you use a cellphone and
press "send," where does the call go to?

531
00:48:25,236 --> 00:48:27,447
- Why are you asking?
- The boss man at fort Howard.

532
00:48:27,530 --> 00:48:30,075
He tosses the cellphone we're up on, right?

533
00:48:30,158 --> 00:48:33,995
Then he pulls out another thingamajig,
and he types a message.

534
00:48:34,120 --> 00:48:36,456
Text messaging.

535
00:48:37,123 --> 00:48:40,794
It starts at one of those towers
they got up all over the place, right?

536
00:48:40,877 --> 00:48:43,546
And ends up in a computer
at a wireless provider.

537
00:48:43,755 --> 00:48:47,842
So if you knew when the call was made
could you trace the call to that tower?

538
00:48:48,551 --> 00:48:50,845
If you could,
mightn't you get a phone number?

539
00:48:51,012 --> 00:48:53,306
Then you got the billing details, right?

540
00:48:53,389 --> 00:48:56,351
Do you have any idea
how many people use cellphones?

541
00:48:56,851 --> 00:48:59,979
There must be hundreds of thousands
at any time.

542
00:49:00,063 --> 00:49:02,857
What you need is another variable.

543
00:49:03,024 --> 00:49:06,653
Another bit of data to help you isolate
your call from all the others.

544
00:49:06,736 --> 00:49:11,074
What if you knew where the call was made?
I mean, exactly where it was made.

545
00:49:11,157 --> 00:49:16,121
Well, we were out in the middle of nowhere.
Does that help narrow it down?

546
00:49:16,204 --> 00:49:20,458
The fort Howard sea wall. It ain't
exactly Charles and Baltimore streets.

547
00:49:20,583 --> 00:49:23,545
You've got another problem.
Which wireless company?

548
00:49:23,628 --> 00:49:27,715
There must be what,
verizon, mci, at&t, sprint...

549
00:49:27,799 --> 00:49:30,927
Shit, tin cans and a string.
You got dozens of them.

550
00:49:39,435 --> 00:49:40,812
Lamar?

551
00:49:41,729 --> 00:49:44,190
- Where's my Harper's?
- Say what?

552
00:49:44,274 --> 00:49:46,109
Harper's. The new issue.

553
00:49:46,192 --> 00:49:50,155
You said the new republic and Atlantic
and a new something else.

554
00:49:50,238 --> 00:49:52,031
I did not forget to tell you Harper's.

555
00:49:52,115 --> 00:49:56,161
Every week I tell you the same shit and
every week you forget half of what I say.

556
00:49:56,870 --> 00:50:00,373
Tomorrow, first thing, you go
to the news stand and you get Harper's.

557
00:50:00,456 --> 00:50:04,169
And the nation, too,
which you also managed to forget.

558
00:50:05,879 --> 00:50:09,841
You know what the most dangerous thing
in america is, right?

559
00:50:11,467 --> 00:50:13,595
A nigger with a library card.

560
00:50:16,181 --> 00:50:19,684
All damn day, he just sit there reading.

561
00:50:20,602 --> 00:50:23,354
And damned if them eastside bitches
don't stay away.

562
00:50:23,438 --> 00:50:26,566
- That's real muscle, right there.
- True that.

563
00:50:27,692 --> 00:50:31,571
What are we gonna do
when we start running out of good product?

564
00:50:31,654 --> 00:50:33,698
That's what we need to ask ourselves.

565
00:50:33,781 --> 00:50:37,035
Yo, bodie,
if stringer want the eastside up in here,

566
00:50:37,619 --> 00:50:40,580
then why barksdale got a man
running them off?

567
00:50:47,754 --> 00:50:49,589
Nothing.

568
00:50:50,924 --> 00:50:54,719
This is getting us nowhere.
We got nothing under pyramid inc.

569
00:50:54,802 --> 00:50:57,263
Or any of the targets
at any other cellular company.

570
00:50:57,347 --> 00:50:59,015
It's on mcnulty then.

571
00:50:59,807 --> 00:51:02,101
11-35, you got the 20?

572
00:51:02,185 --> 00:51:04,979
- I'm on the spot right now.
- Go.

573
00:51:05,480 --> 00:51:10,193
10-4. Latitude first,
north, 39 degrees. 11.727.

574
00:51:10,276 --> 00:51:14,739
Longitude west, 76 degrees. 26.628.

575
00:51:17,325 --> 00:51:21,162
Now, this was a neat trick.
No one ever did it before.

576
00:51:21,246 --> 00:51:24,332
Identified a cellphone using time and GPS.

577
00:51:24,415 --> 00:51:27,085
We got everything on the phone
that was text messaging

578
00:51:27,168 --> 00:51:30,004
from those coordinates
at 16:45 hours today.

579
00:51:35,843 --> 00:51:37,220
Just a subpoena?

580
00:51:37,303 --> 00:51:40,765
With this, you can get account information
and a phone number.

581
00:51:41,140 --> 00:51:46,020
With a search warrant you can get
two months of text messages.

582
00:51:47,355 --> 00:51:49,774
You got two months of text messages
in this file?

583
00:51:49,857 --> 00:51:52,443
I do, if you've got a warrant.

584
00:51:54,028 --> 00:51:55,613
Tell you what, friend.

585
00:51:55,697 --> 00:51:58,741
We're gonna start typing that warrant
tomorrow morning.

586
00:51:58,825 --> 00:52:01,077
But right now,
we wouldn't mind taking a peek

587
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:03,413
